/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-01.md:51:"Material stretching," "joint energy-helicity transfer," "stochastic circulation,"
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:5:This chain is strongest as an obstruction hunt and weak as a positive proof route. Its good instinct is that full 3D Navier-Stokes transports more structure than energy alone, and that same-helicity folklore should not be confused with theorem-relevant leverage. Its main weakness is that it treats "joint energy-helicity flux" as if it were already a candidate coercive mechanism. It is not. Energy is positive and directly tied to standard control. Helicity is sign-indefinite, scale-weighted, and highly vulnerable to cancellation. Unless the chain can produce a one-sided, localization-stable, endpoint-relevant gain from that coupling, it is mostly repackaging cascade geometry.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:18:- The hidden assumption is that energy-helicity coupling contains an additional one-sided quantity that can face a regularity endpoint. But helicity density is sign-indefinite, and global helicity mixes scale and chirality rather than directly controlling the bad local term. That assumption should be tested before the endpoint is frozen, not after.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:27:- Writing the energy and helicity transfer identities is easy relative to the real problem. The hard question is whether any coupled identity yields a one-sided estimate after all admissible signs and localizations are restored. The chain risks mistaking "I have an exact balance law" for "I have isolated a usable mechanism."
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:30:- There is a serious decomposition-dependence problem. In helical or dyadic form, one can often make the joint energy-helicity picture look more informative than it is. If the only Tao-sensitive content is a sign-sensitive triad ledger, then the chain has drifted back into the old folklore it claims to transcend.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:40:- A "forbidden simultaneous transfer pattern" sounds attractive, but it can easily reduce to a triad-sign statement that says certain idealized polarized interactions cannot move energy and helicity in the same way. Full Navier-Stokes does not live on those filtered sectors.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:42:- The prior-art benchmark is correctly requested and still too late. Before promoting any mechanism, the chain should force an explicit statement of what is new relative to Waleffe-type analysis, helical shell-model intuition, and decimated same-sign sectors. Otherwise Step 3 will rediscover known favorable subregimes and mistake them for fresh structural leverage.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:55:- The classification between "real leverage," "partial leverage," and "non-coercive structure" is good discipline, but by Step 4 the damage may already be done. If the earlier steps never required an explicit map from coupled flux to the actual bad term, the reconstruction ledger will mostly record predictable collapse.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:64:- The "first missing lemma" is likely not a routine gap. It is likely the entire hard problem: proving that any favorable energy-helicity geometry persists, localizes, and dominates the bad full-equation interactions.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:78:"Transports both energy and helicity" and "joint transfer geometry" are true, but theorem relevance does not follow from that. Many cascade descriptions are exact and mathematically elegant while remaining useless for continuation or singularity exclusion.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:90:The route lives next to helical triad analysis, decimated models, Waleffe-type interaction lore, and familiar statements that favorable helicity polarization depletes transfer in restricted sectors. Without an early novelty threshold, the chain can spend a lot of effort rediscovering that the favorable regime looks favorable.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:94:The premise already suggests that "the true 3D nonlinearity transports both energy and helicity" should hide a deeper invariant geometry. That is plausible as a heuristic, but it also biases the chain toward believing the coupling must mean more than it may actually mean. A fairer design would treat "exact but non-coercive" as the default hypothesis, not the backup hypothesis.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:105:This is a respectable negative-audit chain and a weak positive chain. Its best contribution is to force a serious answer to a useful question: does exact energy-helicity coupling ever yield a one-sided, localization-stable gain on a named Navier-Stokes bottleneck, or does it collapse into sign-sensitive but non-coercive cascade bookkeeping? My expectation is that the latter is the honest answer.
