/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-003/attacks/chain-01.md:56:Fair point: demanding a named bad term and a predeclared meaning of "real gain" is good discipline. The problem is that the chain does not make those declarations sharply enough.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/attacks/chain-01.md:60:Fair point in its favor: forcing a named bad term and a predeclared notion of gain is good discipline. But as written, this step can screen out live ideas for the wrong reason and screen in dead ones on aesthetic grounds.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-005/attacks/chain-02.md:40:- Naming prior art is necessary but not sufficient. The real risk is not just rediscovering helical decimation or shell-model folklore; it is repackaging known qualitative preferences of same-helicity or near-resonant interactions as if they were new theorem-grade control.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-005/attacks/chain-02.md:48:- "Charge the full cost" is the right instinct, but the chain underspecifies the bill. It needs explicit dyadic summation, angular multiplicity, and the loss from reintroducing all mixed-helicity interactions. Otherwise the stress test stays rhetorical.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-005/attacks/chain-02.md:50:- The perturbation test around favorable helicity or resonance classes is likely fatal. Full Navier-Stokes does not let one isolate clean same-helicity or near-resonant sectors for free. If the gain is only visible on a thin interaction set, then the chain is probably seeing a regime artifact, not a structural mechanism.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-003/attacks/chain-02.md:39:- The listed candidates, such as same-helicity depletion and orientation-specific cancellation, are exactly the sort of mechanisms that already look interesting in spectral language and then often collapse when asked to control a norm. That makes the shortlist vulnerable to choosing what is easy to describe rather than what is live.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-003/judgments/chain-01.md:86:2. Fix one inherited architecture, one exact bad term, one localization protocol, and one bookkeeping currency of gain at the start.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/judgments/chain-01.md:55:This critique lands cleanly. The chain has to choose one inherited architecture at the start, name the exact bad term inside it, and define one bookkeeping notion of gain that all candidates are judged against. Otherwise the shortlist is driven too much by taste and the candidates are not truly comparable.
